    "description": "Peripartum Cardiomyopathy is a rare but serious form of heart failure that occurs during the last month of pregnancy or within five months after delivery. This condition leads to a decrease in the heart's ability to pump blood effectively, which can result in symptoms associated with heart failure. The exact cause is not fully understood, but it is believed to involve a combination of genetic and environmental factors, as well as changes in the hormonal and immune system during and after pregnancy.",
