    "treatments": "Treatment for Peripartum Cardiomyopathy typically involves a combination of medications and lifestyle modifications. Diuretics may be prescribed to help reduce fluid retention. Beta-blockers can improve heart function and control heart rate, while ACE inhibitors may help prevent further heart damage. In some cases, anticoagulants may be used to reduce the risk of blood clots. Beyond medication, lifestyle changes such as a heart-healthy diet, regular exercise, and weight management can be beneficial. In severe cases, hospitalization may be required for more intensive monitoring and treatment. It's critical for affected women to have close follow-up with a cardiologist throughout their recovery."
